Class PlaceKeysValuesInArrayLists<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • tree.PlaceKeysValuesInArrayLists<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K -
    V -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    TraversalTask<K,V>

    public class PlaceKeysValuesInArrayLists<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements TraversalTask<K,V>
    This task places key/values in two arrays in the order in which the key/values are seen during the traversal. If no keys/values are found the ArrayList will be empty (constructor creates two empty ArrayLists).

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      PlaceKeysValuesInArrayLists()
      Creates two ArrayList objects: one for the keys and one for the values.
